article.description: Maodo Lo scored 25 points while distributing 6 assists and Columbia held off Maryland-Eastern Shore by shooting 5 of 6 from the free throw line in the final 22 seconds to post an 81-75 nonconfere
article.headline: Columbia earns 10th win, beats Maryland-Eastern Shore 81-75
article.linkText: Columbia earns 10th win, beats Maryland-Eastern Shore 81-75
article.story: NEW YORK -- Maodo Lo scored 25 points while distributing 6 assists and Columbia held off Maryland-Eastern Shore by shooting 5 of 6 from the free throw line in the final 22 seconds to post an 81-75 nonconference victory Wednesday night. Devin Martin converted two free throws with 46 seconds left to pull Maryland-Eastern Shore (3-14) within two points, 76-74. Nate Hickman and Grant Mullins each hit a pair of free throws and Lo hit the second of two to preserve the victory. Lo scored 10 points in the first 10 minutes, hitting a 3-pointer midway through the first half to give the Lions a 23-20 lead and another with a second left in the half to send Columbia into intermission with a 44-36 advantage. Mullins finished with 15 points for Columbia (10-6) and Jeff Coby added another 11. Dominique Elliott and Martin each scored 21 points to lead the Hawks.
